<font color="#FF0000">VIETNAM WALL</font><br>
<tt>Wed Nov 27 19:25:57 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
The half dozen times that I have been to Washington, I have visited the Wall even though I knew no one who is honored on it.  Of course, it was still an awesome witness to me of the great dedication to duty of so too many persons!  It has taken on the significance of a shrine to me, somewhat like a cemetery.  I have read many of the names, and prayed with tears.  It was just last summer that a friend and I went to Springfield, Illinois to visit the various Lincoln sites.  While at Oak Ridge Cemetery, we came across a very dignified monument honoring those from Illinois who had given &quot;the last full measure&quot; in VietNam.  What would be the possibility of the other states doing likewise in the capitol cities?
<p><code>-- kbw_fry@k12.mec.ohio.gov  (Michael J. Fry) </code><p>


